try the ever-increasing number of chic boutiques in seminyak and support young local designers. jalan laksmana is a good starting point. bali is an island of artisans, so arts and crafts are always popular. try to head to the source if you can rather than buying from identikit shops in kuta or sanur. you will gain more satisfaction from buying an article direct from the maker and seeing the craftsman in action. bali has a huge range of locally produced paintings, basketware, stone and wood carvings, silver and shell jewellery, ceramics, natural paper gifts, glassware and much, much more. dried 